#* {{quote-book|year=1988|author=Andrew Radford|title=Transformational grammar: a first course|location=Cambridge, UK|publisher=Cambridge University Press|page=133}}
#*: Traditional grammar typically recognises a number of further categories: for example, in his ''Reference Book of Terms in Traditional Grammar for Language Students'', Simpson (1982) posits two additional word-level categories which he refers to as ''Particle'', and ''Conjunction''. <b>Particles</b> include the italicised words in '''(58)''' below:
